<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,358,746]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,466,493]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Forewing length is 
<quantity box="[551,695,466,493]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.275" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="1.25" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" unit="mm" value="12.75" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="12.5">12.5–13 mm</quantity>
in males and 
<quantity box="[856,999,466,493]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.475" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.45" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" unit="mm" value="14.75" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="14.5">14.5–15 mm</quantity>
in females. This unmistakable species differs from other relatives by its bright yellow coloration and blackish subterminal area of hindwing. The male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cerny" authorityYear="2016" box="[245,411,539,565]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Barsine" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanovena">
<emphasis box="[245,411,539,565]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">B. melanovena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are similar to those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Volynkin &amp; Černý &amp; Huang, 2019" authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Černý &amp; Huang" authorityYear="2019" box="[671,762,540,565]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Barsine" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mene" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[671,762,540,565]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">B. mene</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[769,833,539,565]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[769,833,539,565]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Volynkin &amp; Černý &amp; Huang, 2019" authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Černý &amp; Huang" authorityYear="2019" box="[847,1020,539,565]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Barsine" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="syntypicoida" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[847,1020,539,565]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">B. syntypicoida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1027,1090,539,565]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1027,1090,539,565]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="♀ Swinhoe" authorityYear="1906" box="[1145,1282,540,565]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Barsine" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="syntypica">
<emphasis box="[1145,1282,540,565]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">B. syntypica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differ by the trigonal and straight medial costal process (that is stronger narrowed distally and slightly curved in other three species), the slightly more robust distal costal process, and the trigonal distal saccular process directed distally-ventrally (that is claw-like curved and directed distally in 
<taxonomicName authority="Volynkin &amp; Černý &amp; Huang, 2019" authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Černý &amp; Huang" authorityYear="2019" box="[760,850,648,673]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Barsine" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mene" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[760,850,648,673]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">B. mene</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[857,921,647,673]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[857,921,647,673]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Volynkin &amp; Černý &amp; Huang, 2019" authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Černý &amp; Huang" authorityYear="2019" box="[935,1108,647,673]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Barsine" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="syntypicoida" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[935,1108,647,673]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">B. syntypicoida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1115,1178,647,673]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1115,1178,647,673]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="♀ Swinhoe" authorityYear="1906" box="[1233,1370,648,673]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Barsine" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="syntypica">
<emphasis box="[1233,1370,648,673]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">B. syntypica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The female genitalia differ clearly from those of other relatives by their broad, wineglass-shaped antrum.
</paragraph>
